<title>
Door Lock Switch and Actuator On-Vehicle Inspection
</title>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Remove door trim.
</ptxt>
<list1 type = "unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>
Front: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A9506011"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>
Rear: 
<intxreftitleoff1 refid = "AENAP70A9506015"><img src = "..\icon\intxreftitleoff.gif"/></intxreftitleoff1>
</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Disconnect door lock connector from door lock assembly.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check door lock switch for continuity between its terminals. Replace door lock assembly if defective.
</ptxt>
</s1>
<s1>
<ptxt>
Check door lock actuator by checking operation of door lock lever when battery voltage is applied to the following terminals of door lock assembly as shown in tables. Replace door lock assembly if defective.
</ptxt>
</s1>
